HEADWORD: Pintsch gas
<hw>Pintsch gas</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[After Richard
<etsep>Pintsch</etsep>, German inventor.]</ety> <def>A kind of oil gas
extensively used for lighting railroad cars, which carry it in
compressed form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

